the second term, b, times 2. I listed the 2 first, since we usually put

00:00:38.771 --> 00:00:44.450
coefficients in front of variables. Now we need to think about the last term,

00:00:44.450 --> 00:00:49.523
the 16 and the 1. Well I know 4 squared is 16, and 1 squared is 1. So to get the

00:00:49.523 --> 00:00:54.459
last term, all I need to do is square the second term. So we square the b, we

00:00:54.459 --> 00:00:59.648
